## 📌 MODULE 1 — Data Understanding & Role Mapping

> **Build Order**: 🥇 First — foundation for everything

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Identify, clean, and standardize all job role categories from the Kaggle dataset |
| **Input** | Raw dataset CSV (2,484 resumes with `Category` column) |
| **Output** | Clean, standardized role label map |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `role_labels` | Standardized list of 25 unique role names |
| `role_distribution` | Count of resumes per role (for class balance analysis) |
| `label_encoding` | Numerical mapping (0–24) for model training |
| `imbalanced_roles` | Roles with < 50 resumes flagged for handling |

### Role Map (from dataset)

| # | Raw Category | Standardized Label | Expected Count |
|---|-------------|-------------------|----------------|
| 1 | HR | HR | ~96 |
| 2 | Designer | Designer | ~96 |
| 3 | Information-Technology | Information Technology | ~96 |
| 4 | Teacher | Teacher | ~96 |
| 5 | Advocate | Advocate | ~96 |
| 6 | Business-Development | Business Development | ~96 |
| 7 | Healthcare | Healthcare | ~96 |
| 8 | Fitness | Fitness | ~96 |
| 9 | Agriculture | Agriculture | ~96 |
| 10 | BPO | BPO | ~96 |
| 11 | Sales | Sales | ~96 |
| 12 | Consultant | Consultant | ~96 |
| 13 | Digital-Media | Digital Media | ~96 |
| 14 | Automobile | Automobile | ~96 |
| 15 | Chef | Chef | ~96 |
| 16 | Finance | Finance | ~96 |
| 17 | Apparel | Apparel | ~96 |
| 18 | Engineering | Engineering | ~96 |
| 19 | Accountant | Accountant | ~96 |
| 20 | Construction | Construction | ~96 |
| 21 | Public-Relations | Public Relations | ~96 |
| 22 | Banking | Banking | ~96 |
| 23 | Arts | Arts | ~96 |
| 24 | Aviation | Aviation | ~96 |

> [!NOTE]
> Dataset has ~2,484 resumes across 25 categories ≈ ~96 per category (roughly balanced).

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: Nothing (first module)
- **Required by**: ALL subsequent modules

---

## 📌 MODULE 2 — Text Preprocessing Pipeline

> **Build Order**: 🥈 Second — required by all models

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Clean and normalize raw resume text for ML consumption |
| **Input** | Raw `Resume_str` text from dataset (or newly uploaded resumes) |
| **Output** | Cleaned, normalized text tokens |

### Processing Steps (WHAT, not HOW)

| Step | Input | Output |
|------|-------|--------|
| HTML Stripping | `Resume_html` or raw text with HTML tags | Plain text |
| Lowercasing | Mixed-case text | All lowercase text |
| Special Character Removal | Text with symbols, URLs, emails | Clean alphanumeric text |
| Stopword Removal | Text with common words (the, is, at) | Content words only |
| Token Normalization | Varied word forms | Standardized tokens |
| Whitespace Normalization | Multiple spaces, tabs | Single-space separated |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `cleaned_text` | Full cleaned text string |
| `tokens` | List of individual processed words |
| `token_count` | Number of tokens (for feature engineering) |
| `char_count` | Character count of cleaned text |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M1 (role mapping for label association)
- **Required by**: M3, M4, M5, M6, M7, M8, M9, M10, M11

---

## 📌 MODULE 3 — Feature Extraction Engine

> **Build Order**: 🥉 Third — converts text to numbers

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Transform cleaned text into numerical feature vectors for ML models |
| **Input** | Cleaned text from M2 |
| **Output** | Numerical feature vectors |

### Feature Types to Generate

| Feature Type | What It Produces | Used By |
|-------------|-----------------|---------|
| **TF-IDF Vectors** | Sparse matrix of term importance | Role classifier, Scorer, Risk predictor |
| **Text Embeddings** | Dense semantic vectors (fixed-size) | Matching engine, Similarity search |
| **Statistical Features** | Token count, unique words, avg word length, section count | Scoring model, Risk model |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `tfidf_vector` | Sparse feature vector (top N terms) |
| `embedding_vector` | Dense vector (e.g., 768-dim) |
| `statistical_features` | Dict of numerical text statistics |
| `combined_features` | Merged feature set for model input |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M2 (cleaned text)
- **Required by**: M4, M6, M7, M8

---

## 📌 MODULE 4 — Role Classification Model

> **Build Order**: 4th — core prediction engine

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Predict the most suitable job role from a resume |
| **Input** | TF-IDF feature vectors from M3 |
| **Output** | Predicted role + confidence scores |

### Model Candidates to Train & Compare

| Model | Why Include |
|-------|------------|
| Multinomial Naive Bayes | Fast baseline for text classification |
| Logistic Regression | Strong linear baseline with probability output |
| Random Forest | Non-linear, handles feature interactions |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `predicted_role` | Single best role (1 of 25 categories) |
| `confidence` | Probability of the predicted role (0.0–1.0) |
| `top_3_roles` | Top 3 roles with individual probabilities |
| `full_distribution` | Probability across all 25 categories |
| `model_used` | Which model produced this prediction |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M3 (feature vectors)
- **Required by**: M6, M9, M10, M11, M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 5 — Skill Extraction Model (AI Version)

> **Build Order**: 4th (parallel with M4) — can be built alongside role classifier

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Extract and categorize skills from resume text using AI pattern recognition |
| **Input** | Cleaned resume text from M2 |
| **Output** | Structured skill inventory |

### What It Extracts

| Skill Category | Examples |
|---------------|----------|
| **Technical Skills** | Python, Machine Learning, SQL, AWS |
| **Soft Skills** | Leadership, Communication, Teamwork |
| **Tools & Platforms** | Git, Docker, Jira, Figma |
| **Domain Knowledge** | Financial Analysis, Healthcare Compliance |
| **Certifications** | AWS Certified, PMP, CPA |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `skills_list` | Flat list of all extracted skills |
| `categorized_skills` | Dict grouped by category |
| `skill_count` | Total number of skills found |
| `category_distribution` | Count per category |
| `proficiency_hints` | Inferred level per skill (based on context frequency) |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M2 (cleaned text)
- **Required by**: M6, M9, M10, M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 6 — Resume Scoring Model

> **Build Order**: 5th — needs M4 and M5 outputs

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Produce a data-driven quality score (0–100) for any resume |
| **Input** | Feature vectors (M3) + Predicted role (M4) + Extracted skills (M5) |
| **Output** | Composite quality score with breakdown |

### Scoring Dimensions

| Dimension | Weight | What It Measures |
|-----------|--------|-----------------|
| **Skill Relevance** | 30% | How well skills match the predicted role |
| **Skill Volume** | 20% | Total number and diversity of skills |
| **Experience Indicators** | 20% | Keywords suggesting work experience depth |
| **Role Alignment** | 15% | Confidence of role classification |
| **Completeness** | 15% | Presence of resume sections (education, projects, etc.) |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `total_score` | 0–100 composite score |
| `dimension_scores` | Individual scores per dimension |
| `percentile_rank` | Position relative to same-role resumes |
| `score_level` | Excellent (80+) / Good (60–79) / Average (40–59) / Weak (<40) |
| `scoring_explanation` | Text explaining score drivers |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M3 (features) + M4 (role) + M5 (skills)
- **Required by**: M7, M10, M11, M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 7 — Risk Prediction Model

> **Build Order**: 6th — needs scoring output

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Predict the probability that a resume will be rejected |
| **Input** | Resume score (M6) + Feature vectors (M3) + Skills data (M5) |
| **Output** | Risk probability and actionable mitigation |

### Risk Factors Analyzed

| Factor | Impact Signal |
|--------|--------------|
| Low skill count | Higher rejection probability |
| Weak role alignment | Poor fit for target positions |
| Missing key sections | Incomplete resume |
| Below-average score | Underperforming vs. peer resumes |
| Low skill diversity | Limited versatility |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `risk_probability` | 0–100% likelihood of rejection |
| `risk_level` | Low (0–30%) / Medium (30–60%) / High (60–100%) |
| `risk_factors` | List of specific weaknesses driving risk |
| `mitigation_actions` | Prioritized suggestions to reduce risk |
| `risk_trend` | Compared to similar-role candidates |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M6 (score) + M3 (features) + M5 (skills)
- **Required by**: M10, M11, M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 8 — Job Description Matching Engine

> **Build Order**: 6th (parallel with M7) — independent of scoring

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Compute semantic similarity between a resume and a job description |
| **Input** | Resume embedding (M3) + Job description text (user-provided) |
| **Output** | Match percentage and breakdown |

### Matching Dimensions

| Dimension | What It Compares |
|-----------|-----------------|
| **Semantic Similarity** | Overall meaning overlap (embeddings) |
| **Skill Match** | Skills in resume vs. skills in JD |
| **Role Alignment** | Predicted role vs. JD target role |
| **Experience Match** | Experience level indicators in both texts |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `match_percentage` | 0–100% overall compatibility |
| `dimension_breakdown` | Score per matching dimension |
| `matching_skills` | Skills found in both resume and JD |
| `missing_skills` | Skills in JD but not in resume |
| `candidate_rank` | Position relative to other candidates for this JD |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M3 (embeddings) + M5 (skills)
- **Required by**: M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 9 — Career Trajectory Model

> **Build Order**: 7th — built after role + skill modules are stable

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Predict likely next career moves based on current profile |
| **Input** | Predicted role (M4) + Extracted skills (M5) |
| **Output** | Future role predictions with transition probabilities |

### Trajectory Sources

| Source | What It Provides |
|--------|-----------------|
| **Cross-role skill overlap** | Roles sharing many skills are natural transitions |
| **Dataset patterns** | Shared skill clusters across different role categories |
| **Skill adjacency** | Skills that frequently co-occur suggest transition paths |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `next_roles` | Top 3–5 predicted next career roles |
| `transition_probability` | Likelihood of each transition (0–100%) |
| `required_skills` | Skills needed to unlock each transition |
| `current_readiness` | % of required skills already present |
| `transition_graph` | Network data for visual career path rendering |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M4 (predicted role) + M5 (skills)
- **Required by**: M10, M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 10 — Digital Twin Simulator (AI Version)

> **Build Order**: 8th — aggregator module, needs all prediction models

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Simulate resume modifications and predict their impact through AI re-prediction |
| **Input** | Current resume + user-specified changes (add skill, change target role, etc.) |
| **Output** | Before/after comparison across all prediction dimensions |

### Simulation Types

| Simulation | What Changes | What Gets Re-Predicted |
|-----------|-------------|----------------------|
| **Add Skill** | Inject a new skill into the resume | Score, Role, Risk, Career paths |
| **Remove Weakness** | Address a flagged risk factor | Risk level, Score change |
| **Target New Role** | Change the target role for gap analysis | Skill gap, Readiness %, Learning path |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `before_state` | Snapshot of all current predictions |
| `after_state` | Snapshot of all predictions after simulation |
| `score_delta` | Numeric change in score |
| `role_shift` | Changes in top-3 role predictions |
| `risk_delta` | Change in risk probability |
| `improvement_summary` | Natural-language explanation of impact |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M4 + M5 + M6 + M7 + M9 (ALL prediction models)
- **Required by**: M11, M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 11 — Explainable AI (XAI) Layer

> **Build Order**: 9th — runs on top of all model outputs

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Generate human-readable explanations for every AI prediction |
| **Input** | Outputs from M4, M6, M7, M9, M10 |
| **Output** | Explanation text + feature importance data |

### Explanation Targets

| Prediction | Explanation Format |
|-----------|-------------------|
| **Role Classification** | "Classified as [role] because: [top contributing features], confidence: [X%]" |
| **Resume Score** | "Score [X/100] driven by: [dimension breakdown with positive/negative factors]" |
| **Risk Level** | "[Risk level] because: [specific weaknesses], mitigate by: [actions]" |
| **Career Trajectory** | "Predicted [role] transition because: [shared skill patterns], readiness: [X%]" |
| **Simulation** | "Adding [skill] would: [impact summary] because [reasoning]" |

### Output Specification

| Output Field | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| `explanation_text` | Full natural-language explanation |
| `feature_importance` | Top features/words contributing to prediction |
| `confidence_factors` | What makes the prediction confident/uncertain |
| `comparison_context` | How this resume compares to others in the same category |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: M4, M6, M7, M9, M10 (all prediction outputs)
- **Required by**: M12

---

## 📌 MODULE 12 — Model Output Storage

> **Build Order**: 10th (final) — persistence layer for all outputs

| Attribute | Definition |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Purpose** | Persist all AI predictions to the dedicated AI database |
| **Input** | Outputs from ALL modules (M4–M11) |
| **Output** | Stored records in `resumes_ai`, `model_outputs`, `similarity_cache` tables |

### Storage Map

| Module Output | Stored In | Key Fields |
|--------------|-----------|------------|
| Role prediction (M4) | `resumes_ai` | `predicted_role`, `confidence` |
| Skills (M5) | `resumes_ai` + `skills_master` | Skill records + associations |
| Score (M6) | `resumes_ai` | [score](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/careerforge%202-%20Copy/analyzer.py#62-142) |
| Risk (M7) | `resumes_ai` | `risk_probability`, `risk_level` |
| Match results (M8) | `model_outputs` | `predictions` (JSON) |
| Career paths (M9) | `model_outputs` | `predictions` (JSON) |
| Simulations (M10) | `model_outputs` | `predictions` (JSON) |
| Explanations (M11) | `model_outputs` | `explanation` |
| Embeddings (M3) | `resumes_ai` | `embeddings` (vector) |

### Dependencies
- **Depends on**: ALL modules (M4–M11)
- **Required by**: Frontend dashboard, Admin insights, Recruiter views

